&lt;p&gt;The Staff Bank for Epsom and St Helier University NHS trust are looking for experienced Band 5 Nurses to work within our Surrey Downs Community Team to work within the team in Leatherhead, contributing to team mangement and the development of innovative practice. To be responsible for the assessment of care needs and the development, implementation and evaluation of holistic care packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great rates, access to the NHS pension, freeCore Skills and the support of a professional and friendly team from the moment you register with us, to your first shift and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join, you must:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Currently be registered with the NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Be eligible to work in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Pass an enhanced DBS check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* A minimum of 6 months&#39; NHS experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to join the Epsom &amp; St Helier NHS Trust family.&lt;/p&gt;
